      "content": "i get the \"balanced approach\" thing but honestly it feels like a bit of an easy answer. if u actually had to pick one to prioritize to prevent a total collapse, which one is the bigger threat? like, is it more dangerous to have a huge debt that might crash the currency, or is it more dangerous to have a massive amount of people living in poverty without support?",
